

    
       
      OK I managed to find out what the stance I always seem to be using during bokken practice is really called. It's Jigo-tai, meaning defensive posture. Term is broadly used in Japanese martial arts besides Aikido, eg. Karate.  Another term is 'Masakatsu agatsu', True victory is Self-victory. In Chinese / Kanji = Zheng4 Sheng4 Wu4 Sheng4. Meaningful, yet so hard to accomplish for so many of us.
       
    
    
